E. COLI EHEC - USA (07): O157, ROMAINE LETTUCE
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 25 Apr 2018
Source: CDC [edited]
https://www.cdc.gov/ecoli/2018/o157h7-04-18/index.html


Since the last update on 18 Apr 2018, 31 more people were added to this outbreak.

As of 25 Apr 2018, 84 people infected with the outbreak strain of _E. coli_ O157:H7 have been reported from 19 states. Illnesses started on dates ranging from 13 Mar 2018 to 12 Apr 2018. Ill people range in age from 1 to 88 years, with a median age of 31. 65 percent of ill people are female. 42 ill people have been hospitalized, including 9 people who developed hemolytic uremic syndrome, a type of kidney failure. No deaths have been reported.

